Colombian Stock Movers: Almacenes Exito, Pacific Rubiales Energy

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-10-21T20:18:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/colombian-stock-movers-almacenes-exito-pacific-rubiales-energy.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3 p.m. local time.  The IGBC Index rose 1.1 percent to 13,507.02 while the
Colcap Index gained 0.5 percent to 1,627.27.  Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  , Colombia’s biggest publicly-
traded retailer, rose 2.4 percent to 23,620 pesos, a one-month
high. The company will release third-quarter results today after
the market closes, spokeswoman Analucia Isaza said in an e-mail
response.  The company said on July 25 its second-quarter profit rose
96 percent from a year ago to 65.6 billion pesos ($35 million).  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, rose 3 percent to
46,260 pesos.  Petrotech Engineering Ltd. said Rubiales has a total of 2.8
billion barrels of oil equivalent in its exploration blocks in
Colombia, Peru and  Guatemala , according to a resource evaluation
report filed with  Colombia ’s securities regulator today.  Rubiales “is in the best position to have some of the most
significant oil discoveries in Colombia in the short and medium
term,” according to a report e-mailed by Juan David Pineros, an
analyst at Interbolsa SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
